== Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Veggies ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @Green Beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds.

Trim the @Pak Choi{1}, then thinly slice widthways.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

== Mince ==

Once hot, add the @British Pork Mince{240%grams} and beans. Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Sauce and Assembly ==

Add the pak choi and garlic to the mince. Stir fry for ~{1%min}.

Stir in the @Gochujang Paste{50%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{100%milliliter} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts). Bring to the boil.

Once boiling, reduce the heat and simmer until the pork is cooked and the sauce has thickened, ~{3-4%mins}. Stir occasionally.

Once the sauce has thickened, remove from the heat. Stir in the @BBQ Sauce{48%grams}.

Taste the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

== To Serve ==

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with the gochujang BBQ mince.

Sprinkle over the @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} to finish.

Enjoy!